Demo template for custom subobject display (Level 4 in
docs/user-guide/customizing-display.md).

Category:Chapter sets `Has subobject display template = ChapterTable`,
so every parent category that embeds Chapter as a subobject routes the
whole Chapter section here instead of invoking the default
per-instance Chapter/subobject-row pipeline. Result: all chapters
appear as rows of one shared wikitable on every parent page.

SMW's `introtemplate=` and `outrotemplate=` are called once each —
only when the `#ask` yields ≥1 result. That means parent pages that
inherit the Chapter subobject field but declare no instances (e.g. a
Textbook with no chapter subobjects yet) leave no trace on the page:
no orphan header, no empty frame.

Parameters:
* category - The subobject category name (passed by the dispatcher).
             Defaults to "Chapter" for direct invocation.
* page     - The parent page whose subobjects to render; defaults to
             {{FULLPAGENAME}}.
</noinclude>
